</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Official website</th>
<td class="" style=""><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.thesun.co.uk/">thesun.co.uk</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><i><b>The Sun</b></i> is a daily national <a href="Tabloid_newspaper" title="Tabloid newspaper" class="mw-redirect">tabloid</a> newspaper published in the <a href="United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a> and <a href="Republic_of_Ireland" title="Republic of Ireland">Ireland</a>. Regionalised editions are published in Glasgow (<i><b><a href="The_Scottish_Sun" title="The Scottish Sun" class="mw-redirect">The Scottish Sun</a></b></i>) and Dublin (<i><b><a href="index.html#The_Irish_Sun" title="The Sun (United Kingdom)">The Irish Sun</a></b></i>). It is published by the <a href="News_Group_Newspapers" title="News Group Newspapers" class="mw-redirect">News Group Newspapers</a> division of <a href="News_International" title="News International">News International</a>, itself a wholly owned <a href="Subsidiary" title="Subsidiary">subsidiary</a> of <a href="Rupert_Murdoch" title="Rupert Murdoch">Rupert Murdoch</a>'s <a href="News_Corporation" title="News Corporation">News Corporation</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-NMASun_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NMASun-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i>The Sun</i> has the tenth-largest <a href="Newspaper_circulation" title="Newspaper circulation">circulation</a> of any newspaper in the world and the largest circulation of any daily newspaper in the United Kingdom.<sup id="cite_ref-circ_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-circ-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> It had an average daily circulation of 2,656,271 copies in September 2012.<sup id="cite_ref-circ_1-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-circ-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Between January and June 2012 the paper had an average daily readership of approximately 7.3&#160;million, with approximately 34% of those falling into the <a href="NRS_social_grade" title="NRS social grade">ABC1</a> demographic and 64% in the <a href="NRS_social_grade" title="NRS social grade">C2DE</a> demographic. The average age of a <i>Sun</i> reader is 45 and approximately 45% of readers are women.<sup id="cite_ref-NMASun_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NMASun-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i>The Sun</i> has been involved in a number of controversies in its history, including its coverage of the <a href="Hillsborough_disaster" title="Hillsborough disaster">Hillsborough football stadium disaster</a>, false allegations against <a href="Elton_John" title="Elton John">Elton John</a>, and its attitude towards mental health issues and homosexuality.</p>
<p>On 26 February 2012, <i>The Sun on Sunday</i> was launched to replace the defunct <i><a href="News_of_the_World" title="News of the World">News of the World</a></i>, employing a number of its former journalists.<sup id="cite_ref-GuardRMemail_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GuardRMemail-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7"><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i>The Sun</i> also has an <a href="IPad" title="IPad">iPad</a> edition that costs £4.99 for a 30-day subscription and an app, priced at 69p.<sup id="cite_ref-iPad_8-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-iPad-8"><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
